# Design considerations

Graphs are not necessarily the best way to display data since they can become
cluttered. A computer can easily render a graph with many edges, but a human
does not necessarily understand the information displayed. See [][#schraefel:2006]
for discussion of the *Big Fat Graph* used in the semantic web.

See also the discussion at <https://github.com/ipfs/dataviz/issues/4>. It talks about the software behind
  - <https://github.com/nodesphere>,
  - <https://github.com/core-network>,
  - <http://dstack.org/learn-more/>.

